<br>
Tactics vary massively, but a few things are constant. You need a core group of high levels, generally that means 60+. You'll want buffs from outside your own group, KEI, Aego, Focus, as many different DS as you can stack (inc potions), mod rods, focus items to increase nuke dmg etc.<br>
<br>
Some things I've heard: <br>
Don't bother with slow. Get a meaty tank with a tonne of high level DS on him and preferably some form of AE taunt. Mobs will do themselves a lot of damage<br>
However, slower essential for the final boss mob who is pretty tough.<br>
Use heals over time, not CH, CH will get healers aggroed fast.<br>
AE tactics are one way that works well.<br>
Another option is melee dps with monk/rogue/bst, perhaps ench for crowd control if tank cant take all mobs at once<br>
Druids/Mages can banish the rocks, 10k in one cast has to be good. Mages also great for pet, nukes, and DS.<br>
Secondary healer very useful for healing the rest of the group.<br>
Some form of nuker is useful if a mob does get to the prisoner, to land that quick kill.<br>
<br>
I'm sure there's loads more, thats from memory and there are a lot of posts about it.<br>
<br>
In summary, it sounds tough, challenging.... and fun! Don't expect to pass first time, it will likely take quite a few attempts to sort out tactics. Requirements are probably level 60 minimum, and preferably lots of AA points too.<br>
