<br>
Here was my groups setup from what I remember.  Had, 60 shaman(me) 65sk (MT), 65 druid, 65 cleric, 64 rog, 65 bard.  Every mob died in about 20 secs, and the boss went down in about 30 secs.  Hell, I had enough time to cast malo, slow then malosini on the mob and he was dead by the time that hte third one died.  If I go back and think about it, this is what I came up with.  Obviously the SK was the MT.  The rogue and the bard assisted him asap.  The bard used his AE mezz and AE mana song, as well as his haste and his song that adds dmg to all nukes (not sure the name of it).  I would throw at least one nuke on each mob, sometimes more, and help a bit with the healing.  I maloed every mob that was around, to help the DPS of the melees...plus the pet was running around in there.  Only once did I grab agro for whatever reason and I got rid of it pretty quickly.  The druid and the cleric were nuking away, with I think the druid healing (I could be wrong, but since it went soo quickly and smoothly, I wasn't even sure).  I even think that the cleric was doing a bit of the meleeing in there.  When the fourth wave is finished, the boss mob will spawn behind you immediately.  Remember that there is going to be about a 10 sec rest in between waves, and the last boss gives you no rest.  As soon as he spawns...he needs to be slowed.  But, you will get a mitigated slow, which means that you can slow him, but it won't be fully effective.  I have no clue how effective, just that I got the message as soon as I cast it.<br>
<br>
Problem with most groups are they do not have the proper people for the fight.  Like it was said, there are classes that are great for this fight, and their are classes that aren't.  Depending on their lvl and equipment or skill, Mages and Wizards are good to have.  I understand that some of you do not have a horse, but you will have no time to sit around and med during the fighting, so a horse is almost essential if you want to have enough mana to cover you for the whole time there.  The fights are soo quick and you have to put out soo much to kill everything quick, you will need to have insane mana regen.<br>
<br>
So, my advice would be to grab at least 4 people that are insane dmg dealers in there, and fill the final two spots with people that need to be flagged.  At least one of those two classes need to be someone that can do some dmg.<br>
